25|$|Officials are {{reported}} to have considered insertion or targeted aerial dropping of boric acid, boronated plastic beads or boron carbide pellets into the spent <b>fuel</b> <b>pools</b> to absorb neutrons. France flew 95 tonnes of boron to Japan on 17 March 2011 and the US has provided 9 tons. Neutron absorbing boric acid has been add to water injected into the reactor cores, but is unclear if boron was included with the spraying of spent <b>fuel</b> <b>pools</b> (SFP)s.|$|R
